{
  "texts": [
    "SEM images show the surface of the AgF at various magnifications and how it is coated with a mesoporous Ag film (AgM) with an average pore size of 28 ± 4 nm in diameter (Fig. 2c-e).",
    "This structure is called AgF@AgM to indicate that the mesoporous Ag metal encapsulates the AgF (Fig. 2).",
    "The electrochemical active surface area (ECSA) of the Ag foam increased by 25% after the formation of the mesoporous Ag layer (Suppl. Fig.",
    "This deposition method is an example of noble metal mesopores deposited directly on large macroscale 3D metal structures.",
    "Hydrophobization of AgF@AgM could increase capillary forces and promote hydrophobic interactions to drive the selectivity toward MPs."
  ]
}